messages.message:
FYI, noticing that confidence scores are getting exposed on the AI Hub results endpoint even if you're not a commercial customer. We should use the auth token info to hide this if you don't have commercial since it's a commercial only feature :lock:

Here's a run result for an app I built with <mailto:avi.vaid@instabase.com|avi.vaid@instabase.com> (community user) on Prod.

I think we should be able to hide this with some of the context switching changes we're introducing @Adam @naveen.

The commercial features should only be shown if the app is being run in an org. If an app is being run in community account, a user shouldn't be able to see this.
@andy @Wilson should we lump results API changes into the planned API work?
no, weâ€™re planning on tackling Results API after the File Abstraction work
